    "body": "If you don't want to use a snapshot and keep current properties than there is no reason to create a fork. Just start a [private network](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Private-network).\r\n\r\n1. They are scattered in the code base, the `params` and `cmd/utils` package are good places to start.\r\n2. `ethdb` package, but you can change the default location with the `--datadir` flag.\r\n3. most of it is in `internal/ethapi`\r\n\r\n> Also I would like to know \"What ethereum's network id do\"\r\n\r\nClients only connect to each other when they talk the same protocol version and network id.",
